  <!-- LEGAL OBLIGATIONS -->
  <section class="pf-section" style="background:#f8fafc;">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>St Helens Landlords. This Is a Legal Requirement.</h2>
      <p class="pf-sub">Under the <a href="https://www.hse.gov.uk/gas/landlords/index.htm" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Gas Safety (Installation and Use) Regulations 1998</a>, every St Helens landlord must hold a valid CP12 for every rental property containing gas appliances. Non-compliance carries serious legal and financial consequences.</p>

      <div class="pf-who-grid" style="margin-top:2rem;">
        <div class="pf-who-item" style="border-left:3px solid #dc2626;">
          <div style="background:#dc2626;color:#ffffff;font-family:'Barlow Condensed',sans-serif;font-weight:900;font-size:1rem;min-width:1.75rem;height:1.75rem;border-radius:50%;display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:center;flex-shrink:0;">1</div>
          <div><strong>Fines up to £6,000 per property</strong><p>The <a href="https://www.hse.gov.uk" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Health and Safety Executive</a> and St Helens Council both enforce gas safety compliance. A single non-compliant property can result in a fine up to £6,000. Criminal prosecution is possible. A CP12 costs £80.</p></div>
        </div>
        <div class="pf-who-item" style="border-left:3px solid #dc2626;">
          <div style="background:#dc2626;color:#ffffff;font-family:'Barlow Condensed',sans-serif;font-weight:900;font-size:1rem;min-width:1.75rem;height:1.75rem;border-radius:50%;display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:center;flex-shrink:0;">2</div>
          <div><strong>A lapsed or incomplete CP12 blocks a Section 21 notice</strong><p>A lapsed certificate and an incomplete certificate both carry the same Section 21 risk. Courts have ruled CP12 compliance is a legal prerequisite for a valid Section 21. An uninspected gas fire makes your certificate incomplete for this purpose.</p></div>
        </div>
        <div class="pf-who-item" style="border-left:3px solid #dc2626;">
          <div style="background:#dc2626;color:#ffffff;font-family:'Barlow Condensed',sans-serif;font-weight:900;font-size:1rem;min-width:1.75rem;height:1.75rem;border-radius:50%;display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:center;flex-shrink:0;">3</div>
          <div><strong>Certificate must be provided to tenants within 28 days</strong><p>You must provide a copy of the valid CP12 to existing tenants within 28 days of issue and to new tenants before they move in. We email the digital certificate the same day so you can forward it to your St Helens tenants immediately.</p></div>
        </div>
        <div class="pf-who-item" style="border-left:3px solid #dc2626;">
          <div style="background:#dc2626;color:#ffffff;font-family:'Barlow Condensed',sans-serif;font-weight:900;font-size:1rem;min-width:1.75rem;height:1.75rem;border-radius:50%;display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:center;flex-shrink:0;">4</div>
          <div><strong>Certificate must be renewed every 12 months</strong><p>A CP12 is valid for 12 months. If renewed between 10 and 12 months after the previous one, the new certificate runs from the old one's expiry date, preserving the full 12 months without any gap. We add all St Helens landlords to our annual reminder list.</p></div>
        </div>
        <div class="pf-who-item" style="border-left:3px solid #dc2626;">
          <div style="background:#dc2626;color:#ffffff;font-family:'Barlow Condensed',sans-serif;font-weight:900;font-size:1rem;min-width:1.75rem;height:1.75rem;border-radius:50%;display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:center;flex-shrink:0;">5</div>
          <div><strong>Records must be kept for two years</strong><p>Landlords must keep a gas safety record for two years and produce it to the HSE, local authority or tenant on request. We email the digital certificate the same day, creating a permanent timestamped record.</p></div>
        </div>
        <div class="pf-who-item" style="border-left:3px solid #dc2626;">
          <div style="background:#dc2626;color:#ffffff;font-family:'Barlow Condensed',sans-serif;font-weight:900;font-size:1rem;min-width:1.75rem;height:1.75rem;border-radius:50%;display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:center;flex-shrink:0;">6</div>
          <div><strong>HMO licensing in St Helens requires a valid CP12</strong><p>A valid CP12 covering all gas appliances is a mandatory requirement for any HMO licence. St Helens Council's housing enforcement team actively inspect HMO properties and check gas safety compliance as a priority.</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>


