  <!-- FIRST-TIME LET SECTION -->
  <section class="pf-section" style="background:#f1f5f9;">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>First-Time Landlords in St Helens. What You Need Before Your Tenant Moves In.</h2>
      <p class="pf-sub">St Helens has a growing buy-to-let market, particularly in WA10 and WA12. If you are renting out a property for the first time, here is what you need before any tenant can move in.</p>
      <div class="pf-card pf-card-orange" style="margin-top:2rem;">
        <h3>Before Your First Tenant. Your CP12 Checklist.</h3>
        <p>A CP12 gas safety certificate is required before any tenant moves in. The new tenant must receive a copy on or before the tenancy start date, not within 28 days as for renewals, but before day one. If your property has a gas fire, back boiler or gas hob alongside the boiler, all of these must be on the certificate. A certificate that only covers the boiler is not sufficient.</p>
