      <h2>Gas Safety Certificate St Helens. Your Questions Answered</h2>
      <p class="pf-sub">Straight answers to what St Helens landlords and homeowners ask most.</p>
      <div class="pf-faq">
        <details class="pf-faq-item"><summary><span class="pf-faq-tag pf-tag-orange">COST</span>&nbsp; How much does a gas safety certificate cost in St Helens?</summary><div class="pf-faq-body"><p>A CP12 gas safety certificate costs £80 for the first gas appliance, with additional appliances at £10 each. A combined gas safety certificate and annual boiler service costs £175 in a single visit. Portfolio rates from £70 per property for two or more properties. No call-out fee on any visit.</p></div></details>
        <details class="pf-faq-item"><summary><span class="pf-faq-tag pf-tag-red">GAS FIRE</span>&nbsp; Does the CP12 need to cover the gas fire in the living room?</summary><div class="pf-faq-body"><p>Yes. The Gas Safety Regulations 1998 require every gas appliance supplied by the landlord as part of the tenancy to be individually inspected and recorded on the CP12. A gas fire in the living room is a landlord-supplied gas appliance and must be on the certificate. A CP12 that only covers the boiler and not the gas fire is legally incomplete. This is the most common compliance gap we find in St Helens rental properties, particularly in WA10 Victorian terraces. We inspect every appliance in one visit at £10 per additional appliance.</p></div></details>
        <details class="pf-faq-item"><summary><span class="pf-faq-tag pf-tag-navy">SECTION 21</span>&nbsp; Does an incomplete CP12 affect a Section 21 notice?</summary><div class="pf-faq-body"><p>Yes. An incomplete certificate, one that does not cover every gas appliance, carries the same Section 21 risk as no certificate at all. Courts have ruled that CP12 compliance is a legal prerequisite for a valid Section 21. For St Helens landlords with properties containing gas fires, an unchecked fire makes the CP12 legally insufficient for Section 21 purposes.</p></div></details>
        <details class="pf-faq-item"><summary><span class="pf-faq-tag pf-tag-orange">FIRST TIME</span>&nbsp; What does a first-time St Helens landlord need before renting out?</summary><div class="pf-faq-body"><p>A valid CP12 covering every gas appliance in the property must be provided to the new tenant on or before the tenancy start date, not within 28 days, but before they move in. If the property has a gas fire or gas hob alongside the boiler, all must be on the certificate. We can often attend within 24 to 48 hours and email the complete certificate the same day.</p></div></details>
        <details class="pf-faq-item"><summary><span class="pf-faq-tag pf-tag-green">GAS SAFE</span>&nbsp; Are you Gas Safe registered for St Helens CP12 certificates?</summary><div class="pf-faq-body"><p>Yes. Ideal Plumbing Solutions is Gas Safe registered. Verify at <a href="https://www.gassaferegister.co.uk" target="_blank" rel="noopener">gassaferegister.co.uk</a>. All CP12 inspections across St Helens are carried out by our own directly employed Gas Safe registered engineers. We never use sub-contractors.</p></div></details>
        <details class="pf-faq-item"><summary><span class="pf-faq-tag pf-tag-orange">RENEWAL</span>&nbsp; Is there a grace period for renewing a St Helens CP12?</summary><div class="pf-faq-body"><p>Yes. If renewed between 10 and 12 months after the previous certificate, the new certificate runs from the old certificate's expiry date, not the inspection date, preserving the full 12 months without any gap. We add all St Helens landlords to our annual reminder list so you can take advantage of this grace period without accidentally letting the certificate lapse.</p></div></details>
